{c5}(You're a better man than I thought. Alright then, take care of the children 'til I get back.){/c}
A million thanks! How can I possibly repay you?

Great, it's enough that I can use it to help the child! Thank you! I'll take care of it from here on out. Because of your help, maybe this kid will look back one day and think of me as a good person. I feel like it's something I've gotta do, especially considering what I've done in the past.
{c5}(What DID you do in the past?){/c} 
Oh...it's nothing I really want to talk about. But anyway, I need to reward you. I'll have to unpack my bag to see what I've got, so talk to me in a bit. I have so many things in my bag from my many journeys....

Thank you so much. If the boy lives, it's all because of you. That little guy...he's still got his whole life to experience. If he bows out right now...that just ain't right. You've helped one of the true "innocents" in this war. As a reward...I think I have some armors in my bag. Let me pull out a couple of them you might find appealing. 
{c5}(Aksen riffles through his bag.){/c}
Actually...I used to hate kids. They were a nuisance and a liability in battle, and they always shout so loud. But five years ago....I was in the frontier and the Union of Light attacked Huigronn. An arrow whizzed right by me and struck a kid who was close. The boy was just a ransom - he was a kid from the Union of Light. I regretted the fact that an innocent child basically died at my hands. I've probably seen the last of my days as a soldier. When the child has healed, I plan to leave the army. My sin burdens me... Anyway, here we go. I think this armor would suit you well. I'll get more items and equipment, so talk to me later.

-Waiting for a Challenger-
My name is {c2}Berper Yacon{/c}. With my patented BEAR FIST, I'm the strongest in the land! Most folks fight using weapons, but not me! Y'see, even in this modern age, the body is still the most powerful weapon. And to strengthen your body, you've gotta strengthen your spirit. Am I right? You want to prove the power of weapons? Then you'll have to prove your strength first. If you can beat me, I'll reward you with a useful item. 
{c5}(What nonsense. It's more like a flyer than an actual challenge. He's not terribly persuasive, but there's a reward, so maybe it's worth a shot. His condition is to capture certain numbers of {c1}Genetick Poison Mist Zombies{/c}. Now...shall I give it a go?){/c}

You seem to have risen to my challenge. However, you are too weak to argue. Therefore, I'm going to ignore what you're saying. 
{c5}(No, I'm just in this for a reward..){/c}
Denied! My ears are impervious to the babblings of the weak!
{c5}(He's either got a massive ego...or he's just your garden-variety nutcase.){/c}
Whatever happened, I'm a man of my word. I keep my wor,d even if it's a promise with the weak. 
{c5}(Hey...you keep saying that I'm weak, but you...){/c}
Silence! I'll go fetch your prize, so you may speak to me when I get back.

At least you have the ability to match my pace. Good! I respect the powerful. If you didn't have abilities comparable to mine, it wouldn't be worth talking with you. Anyway, you came here because you wanted to throw down in a heated argument, right?
{c5}(No, I'm here for a reward...){/c}
What's this? A secret case of narrow-mindedness? You want to argue, but you keep making excuses.
{c5}(Really, I'm just here for the reward.){/c}
Alright. I get it now. And I'm taking it on myself to correct your narrow-minded behavior. I'll give you a new assignment guaranteed to improve both spirit and mind. Oh, you don't have to thank me - I'm a considerate person by my very nature. 
{c5}(What kind of stubborn jackass is he?){/c}
We're currently experiencing signs of a food shortage due to the threats of war. Therefore, a continual supply and production are important. That's why I decided on the food-growing industry. What I need now is a {c3}Hoe{/c}. 
{c5}(Is he saying he wants...a hoe?){/c}
That's right. A {c3}Hoe{/c}. I'd work that {c3}Hoe{/c} all day. I want to use my hoe and plant seeds. Grain contains a lot of nutrients useful for our body, so it'd be good if we had a lot. I don't know a lot about the process, but I DO know I have strength! How do I know? It's 'cause of my body's finely-tuned reaction! *mumbles*
{c5}(Okay, I get it! I'll go get it, so stop with it already - I'll be back soon enough.){/c}
Psssh...what extreme views you've got. Anyway, I'll see you later, then.

Hmm... At first, you looked kind of powerful, but now you just look so-so. Anyway, you at least have the potential to become strong, so try hard to become like me. Try hard! Then, I'll reward you with crops my awesome harvesting has yielded.
{c5}(Uh...wait a minute here...){/c}
Haha! I'm kidding~ Where's your sense of humor? If you keep such a straight face all the time, life will be a pain. For accepting the challenge, I'll reward you with a good item virtually guaranteed not to disappoint. There was a guy I fought in the past that ended up being too weak. He acknowledged his defeat, so I stripped him of all his armor and sent him on his way. Wasn't that grand and generous of me? You'd probably feel the same, right? Ah, truly. 
{c5}(Is that generosity? It sounds more like...highway robbery....){/c}
Now, I'll give you some goodies from my armor stash. I've gotta go through 'em first, so talk to me a bit later.

How can you do such a pleasing thing? Actually...I like it! A man's gotta be strong like you. For me, I reckon weapons don't matter that much in a fight. If you have the fist and sharp focus, you can even triumph against a dragon. So far, I've fought countless warriors, using just my bare fists. The opponents were quite strong. However, I believe in the passion concentrated into these fists! I will defeat all the fighters in this world and break into the beautiful future! It's 'cause I'm strong! To me, you seem like you're not too far away for my level. Maybe you'll be even stronger someday. When that day comes, our strong wills will surely collide. Guahaha...I'm getting all fired up!
Oh, don't you have any interest in rewards or praise? Apparently not...you're just a hard worker without a sense of greed. You...you'll definitely become strong!
{c5}(Well...actually, I wanted to tell him I'm here ONLY for rewards, but he just kept rambling on like that...){/c}
What's that your mumbling? Anyway, I've gotta reward you. While you were on your mission, that blacksmith, {c2}Siren Dearna{/c} of the Asteria Corps camp has been holding onto your stuff. I wasn't sure of your job, so I put out a range for you to pick from. It was fun talking to you. The result is...waht I said was right! Hahaha~! See you around, my special amigo!
{c5}(Why did I fulfill his requests? Why am I even listening to all this? I'm so confused...){/c}

Uh...hello there! Are you from another village? 
{c5}(I suppose you could say that. And you?){/c}
Oh~ I was right! I've never seen you before. Teehee~ Anyway, my name is {c2}Ruth Merdi{/c}~! Pleased to meet you~
{c5}(Well...why did you call me?){/c}
Actually... I want to leave this place. My parents...they died in a battle. Now I live alone. My dream is to travel aaaalll over, teehee~ 'Cause of that, I wanna help other kids like me.
{c5}(His parents are dead but he's done pretty well for himself. This kid looks strong.){/c}
Since you look pretty tough, I'd like to make a request. Actually, I haven't had the chance to look around the Arian area, so I plan to start from the north and travel all around Adrian. However, I don't know about other monsters, but those {c1}Kalado West Wind Harpies{/c} can really ruin a good day, y'know. If you could take 'em out, that'd really make my travels easier. Could you help me?
{c5}(Ok...this looks like it'd be fine. I'll help){/c}
Really? Thank you~! Teehee~ I haven't got much, but I'll try my best to reward you! See you soon~

Heehee~ Now, 'cause of your help, I can walk freely in that area you cleared. I haven't got many friends my age around here, so I usually walk by myself. I might look weak, but I'm pretty quick! Anyway, I've gotta reward you, but what can I give? Hmmm.....
{c5}(He's hiding, but he limps along like that.){/c}
Oh, this? When I went to check out that area, I got attacked. When I asked the elders of the village, they told me it could've been worse. I don't have a family to worry about me, though, so I'm thinkin' I'll just leave on a trip. 
{c5}(It's dangerous to leave it like that! I'll get the medicine, so wait here.){/c}
Really? Aaaah, I'm ok~ It's nothing... 
{c5}(I think it's obviously something, so, listen to me.){/c}
Ah...thank you. Thank you so much.
{c5}(Just wait a bit. I'll be back with the medicine.){/c}
Hooray~! 
{c5}(I might need {c3}Magic Alchemy Powder{/c}. Perhaps the {c1}Kalado West Wind Harpies{/c} might have them. How many do I need?){/c}

My leg...it's actually okay! Does that mean I can go on an adventure too? Really? 
{c5}(Well...it's a bit soon for that. Maybe in a couple days.){/c}
Really? Tha...Thank you so much!! My dreams came true! Can I leave the village? There are no monsters and I'm ready! I can achieve my dreams! How can I thank you? Should I prepare for the trip? Or...should I say goodbye to others? Shucks, I'm so excited I can't even prioritize! But before anything else, I've gotta reward you~ I'll get what I have prepared. Come and talk to me when I get back!

{c5}(A crumpled paper - crumpled on purpose, no doubt!){/c}
-Resignation Order---
From this date forward, {c2}Pai Johns{/c} is hereby dismissed from active military duty. He is no longer allowed access to military provisions, and shall be treated as a plain civilian.
{c5}(This seems pretty important. I probably ought to return it to the owner. If it's a dismissed soldier, I wonder whose decision it was for him to leave the military....){/c}

{c5}(Dressed like a laborer?){/c}
Why don't you say anything? Why did...wait, where did you get that paper? Where did you get it?!
{c5}(I found it in the northern plains.){/c}
Hmmph. I'm a soldier! I don't need that. The truth is, the army wants to test the person who took that paper, so go directly to the north and hunt down {c1}Kalado Harpies{/c}. Fifteen is the minimum; any more than that is up to you. Now go; you're on Army time now!

Oh my... You're quite the competent soldier, aren't you? (whispering) I wanted to keep his mouth shut... Damn...
{c5}(I didn't quite catch that, did you say something?){/c}
No, Nothing!! Haha!! Beautiful weather we're having, don't you think?! Haha!
{c5}(Really? It looks like a black cloud is...){/c}
Hmmm... really fascinating. Anyway soldier, You've got another test. Hunt down at least 15 {c1}Kalado Tatoramo{/c} and report back to me when you're done! Don't expect much if you fail this one! Better get moving!

Hahaha!! I miss this! I was gonna reward you when you passed the test!! Hahaha!!
{c5}(You seem pretty happy.){/c}
Heh...hehe! Not at all soldier... It hurts my feelings to know the results. Anyway... Come back later! When you grow up! And another thing... If the authorities ask about me, tell them I'm working undercover. I.. I'm in the middle of completing my mission and oooonly the top brass know about this! Haha.. I'll reward you for your silence, Haha! Talk to me later.

Damn... Er, Right.. You did great.. Right.. Damn right.. You've done wonderfully...
{c5}(Thank you, so did I pass?){/c}
Hmm... I'm so happy... Very happy... I'll go get your reward... So while you're waiting can you hunt down and bring me 10 {c1}WedgeRock Tatoramo{/c} and {c1}WedgeRock Tatoramo Trainer{/c} in the north eastern area? This is another part of your test... Good luck! (whispering) Hopefully these will be strong enough this time. lose. a lot.
{c5}(What?){/c}
I said you'd be strong enough to pound those losers a new gut! Come back safely, Soldier...

Why... Why are these things here? Why do {c1}Fedion Black Feet Fox{/c}es have them? 

{c5}(When you carefully looked at the goods...){/c}

This must be the supplies for {c2}Supplier Lanuth{/c} in Arktuis village from Haltek farm. Seeing it here means monsters must have attacked and raided the goods. This is a big problem as the soldiers fighting in the frontline often experience food shortages. I have to inform {c2}Chief Duster{/c} at Haltek farm as soon as possible.

{c5}(After situation has been explained to the chief...){/c}

Hmmm... So, this is how you got here. As I mentioned to you before, our village supplies goods to the Military and you are not allowed to speak about it to anyone. If you do, your life will be in danger. This is for your own sake.

Perhaps I went on too long. You have found the goods that were taken by monsters. However, the fact of the matter is that you now know our secret... Life imprisonment is not unheard of in these cases. However, I'll keep this as our little secret. After seeing you fight those monsters and bringing back the supplies, you're pretty good fighter with a good conscience. It would be a waste to just throw someone of promise behind bars... So, What do say about being in charge of the guarding and delivery of the goods? You can earn some decent salary and do some good for your country on top of not being on the inside of a jail cell for a long time. How could you say no to that, eh? You could even say it's so good that you just can't refuse. Well, take these supplies to {c2}Supplier Lanuth{/c} as soon as possible.

